-- U.S. gold futures rise to record $1,013/oz
-- 
-- Sun Mar 16, 2008 7:50pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/16/us-markets-gold-record-idUST29015720080316

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Gold futures in New York rose to a record high of $1,013 in electronic trading on Monday, on deepening worries about financial markets. 

 At 7:35 p.m. EDT, the active gold contract for April delivery GCJ8 on the Comex division of the New York Mercantile Exchange was at $1,011.5 compared to the New York close of $999.50, after hitting a record high of $1,009. (Reporting by  Miho Yoshikawa ; Editing by  Rodney Joyce )